  "text": "The framework suggests a matrix that reflects the relative weights representing the relationship between all aspects in each pillar. These relationships also indicate the importance of each aspect relative to other aspects as shown in the following matrices. The relative weight of each aspect is measured using an analytical hierarchy process (AHP) (Garbie et al. 2008a and b; [CITATION_1] Garbie and Shikdar 2011a and b) . The relative weights using AHP are estimated and changed frequently according to the new circumstance determined by a decision maker or a group of decision makers [CITATION_2] as shown in Eqns.",
